      "rationale": "Systematic h-refinement study conducted across three mesh densities (coarse ~180k elements, medium ~420k, fine ~910k). GCI-based extrapolation yielded discretization uncertainty of 1.1% on stiffness QoI. Fine mesh adopted for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals below 1e-6 for all load steps; energy balance error <0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson nonlinear solver residuals monitored each load increment; all runs converged to residual norm <1e-7. Energy balance error remained below 0.05% across all 11 construct simulations."
